- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the logical form of non-idempotent intersection types. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as intersection types are a tool used in the analysis of lambda-terms and functional programs. 
- cs.TL (Type Theory) is another possible category as the paper discusses intersection types and their relationship to logical systems. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the analysis of lambda-terms and functional programs, which are related to natural language processing. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a possibility as the paper discusses the formalization of intersection types in a logical system.
